buff-menu.el:

list-buffers-directory needs a documentation string (and thus needs to be
defvar'ed).

list-buffers tracks buffers not by their identity, but by their name.  That
means that if a buffer is renamed (say, by uniquify), it cannot be found
via the buffer-menu, even if it still exists.
Rather than using a 'buffer-name text property that records the buffer
name, use a 'buffer (or some other name) text-property that records the
buffer itself.
You might consider using the buffer name as a backup, but that's not even
as good as using the file name instead.  (Then you could read the file back
in if it isn't at the moment, which might be a nice feature.)  Or, don't
bother to have a backup at all.

