Function vm-fill-paragraphs-containing-long-lines conflates two distinct
concepts:
 * what lines are long enough that they must be re-filled
 * what the fill column should be

My correspondents may use wider lines than I for hand-formatted text, and I
don't want to disturb those.  But I want to fill all their really long
lines, that are definitely wrapped text, and I want those to fit on my
screen.  So, I would like to be able to specify the two concepts
separately.  This was possible in VM 7.19, and it only requires this patch,
plus possibly a way to give the behavior that both variables have the same
value.

--- /DS/home-0/mernst/emacs/vm-8.0.11-581/lisp/vm-misc.el	2008-08-11 22:42:57.000000000 +0200
+++ -	2008-08-22 09:40:17.405632166 +0200
@@ -882,7 +882,6 @@
 (defun vm-fill-paragraphs-containing-long-lines (len start end)
   (let ((done nil)
 	(buffer-read-only nil)
-	(fill-column vm-paragraph-fill-column)
 	;; user doesn't want long lines, so set this to zero for them.
 	(filladapt-fill-column-forward-fuzz 0))
     (save-excursion

